Illustration of Alzheimer's pathology removed because it was entirely misleading and wrong, showing an "amyloid plaque" coating the surface of a neuron (they are accumulations away from cells), "neurofibrillary tangles" on the outside of the neuron cell body (they are inside the cell), and "cortical atrophy" as myelin "corrosion" (it is reduced tissue volume due to cell death). None of these depictions are even partially correct. See https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2918894/
